ses located on Margin Mentor (together the “Service”), you agree to be bound by this Agreement, whether you are a “Visitor” (which means that you simply browse the Margin Mentor website) or you are a “Member” (which means that you have registered with Margin Mentor). The term “you” or “User” refers to a Visitor or a Member. The term “we” refers to Margin Mentor. If you wish to become a Member, communicate with other Members and make use of the Service, you must read this Agreement and indicate your acceptance during the Registration process.\r\n\r\nYou may not use the Service and you may not accept this Agreement if you are not of a legal age to form a binding contract with Margin Mentor.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nIf you accept this Agreement, you represent that you have the capacity to be bound by it or if you are acting on behalf of a company or entity that you have the authority to bind such entity. Before you continue, you should print or save a local copy of this Agreement for your records.\r\n<p align="right"><b>Back to Top</b></p>\r\n<b>2. Privacy and your Personal Information</b>\r\n\r\nFor information about Margin Mentor’s data protection practices, please read Margin Mentor Privacy and Security Policy, which is hereby incorporated into this Agreement. This policy explains how Margin Mentor treats your personal information when you access Margin Mentor and use the Service. The policy may be updated from time to time at our discretion. Changes will be effective upon posting to the site.\r\n<p align="right"><b>Back to Top</b></p>\r\n<b>3. Description of the Service</b>\r\n\r\nThe Service is a business finance information management service that allows Members to consolidate and track their financial information on Margin Mentor. Based on such information, the Service may also present information relating to third party products or services (“Margin Mentor Offers”).\r\n\r\nThe Service is provided to you by Margin Mentor for a prescribed fee and is meant as an aid t